 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Someone on the bank said a god hid me.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Kamikakushi. The valley says it of every man the river takes and every child who runs off. Let them say it; it comforts them and costs you nothing. What took you was water.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"My hands know a knot. I'll keep that.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "You"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You tie it in the cord of your own bedding: a carrier's hitch, fast and one-handed, twice. Sōan watches it both times. He does not write it down while you are looking.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Sōan"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — The Carrier's Hitch: fast, one-handed, holds wet. (+1 AGI / −1 INT)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Standing. Day four; the book said three, so the book gains a line. I am Genemon, steward of the Kurosawa — what this house still has, I count, and you are counted in it now. Ask what you must; the entry is not closed.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What house is this?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"The Kurosawa. Samurai on the lord's rolls; in the granary, near nothing. Both facts are in the book.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"What work is there?\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Rice, half a season's, spilled where the kura door gave in the rains. Rakes; hauls. Wage: meals — that line is already written.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Write me down for the heaviest of it. I'll carry it.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Nameless"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"Written: one back, offered whole; set to the heaviest. Sure hands over quick ones — the book keeps what stays lifted.\"",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "milestone",
   "text": "Perk unlocked — Genemon's Charge: Honest muscle set plainly to the task — sure over nimble. (+1 STR / −1 AGI)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You can stop now, when the day is done — set the work down, and let the body take back what it can.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Clear it without my standing over you, and you'll have earned your rice and a dry corner to sleep in. I'll make you no grander promise than that. In this house, none of us holds one.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"...You don't shirk the work,\" Genemon says, eyeing the cleared boards and the filling basket. \"The house has had its fill of hands that do. Earn your keep, and a place here is yours.\"",
   "count": 1
  }
